message.content:
cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - This paper focuses on the performance of a Spatial Pooler (SP) of a Hierarchical Temporal Memory (HTM) in the task of noisy object recognition. This falls under the domain of neural computing and hence, cs.NE is the most likely category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with the task of object recognition in noisy videos, which is a sub-domain of computer vision. Hence, cs.CV is also a likely category.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a SVM classifier and experiments with different macro parameters of HTM SP to evaluate the performance of the system. This falls under the domain of machine learning and hence, cs.LG is also a likely category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with the task of object recognition in noisy videos using a custom-designed system based on HTM SP, which is a sub-domain of artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely category.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of different macro parameters of HTM SP on the performance of the system, which involves the analysis and monitoring of the system performance. This falls under the domain of information theory and hence, cs.IT is also a likely category.
